headline: Billionaire Warren Buffett Sold 39% of Berkshire's Stake in Bank of America and Is Loading Up on a Famed Consumer Brand That's Skyrocketed 7,700% Since Its IPO
summary: The Oracle of Omaha has sold more than 401 million shares of Bank of America stock since mid-July 2024, and has built up a 7.7% stake in a well-known, consumer-facing business.
